</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1319220-is-this-a-pretty-typical-book-for-the">See all 2 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/35228486-ian-cooper"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1603553206i/35228486._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/35228486-ian-cooper">Ian Cooper</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Book one is a bit tough to get through. Book 2 is better, book 3 is even better, and by book 4, Lindsey Davis&apos;s writing is fully mature. Writers new t<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Book one is a bit tough to get through. Book 2 is better, book 3 is even better, and by book 4, Lindsey Davis's writing is fully mature. Writers new to her books may want to start with her (much later) Flavia Albia books and come back to Falco when they're sure they like her writing style.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
