        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2009122806" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16828527937948272654">Enjoyable read, a first in this historical fiction mystery series set in 1st Century Rome. I felt as if I was reading a 1940&apos;s or 50&apos;s detective novel but with a toga wearing protagonist. Helena, a Roman Senator&apos;s daughter, becomes his unlikely partner in trying to track down a murderer involved in a scheme that siphons silver intended for the Emperor&apos;s treasury.</span>
  <span id="freeText16828527937948272654" style="display:none">Enjoyable read, a first in this historical fiction mystery series set in 1st Century Rome. I felt as if I was reading a 1940's or 50's detective novel but with a toga wearing protagonist. Helena, a Roman Senator's daughter, becomes his unlikely partner in trying to track down a murderer involved in a scheme that siphons silver intended for the Emperor's treasury.</span>
